question:
Analyze the following code snippet and explain in detail the behavior and potential issues related to both type inference and inheritance. Conclude with best practices for using 'var' in an inheritance hierarchy.

```java
class Animal { void speak() { System.out.println("Animal sound"); } }
class Dog extends Animal { 
    @Override void speak() { System.out.println("Bark"); }
    void fetch() { System.out.println("Fetching..."); }
}

public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        var myPet = new Dog();
        myPet.speak();
        myPet.fetch(); // Line A

        myPet = new Animal(); // Line B
    }
}
```
